<div class="definition" id="definition-AME" acro="AME" titletext="Algebraic Multiplicity of an Eigenvalue">
<h5 class="definition">
<span class="type">Definition </span><span class="acro">AME</span> <span class="titletext"> Algebraic Multiplicity of an Eigenvalue</span>
</h5>
<p>Suppose that $A$ is a square matrix and $\lambda$ is an eigenvalue of $A$.  Then the <em class="term">algebraic multiplicity</em> of $\lambda$, $\algmult{A}{\lambda}$, is the highest power of $(x-\lambda)$ that divides the characteristic polynomial, $\charpoly{A}{x}$.</p>
